ion, the author argues that their consumptive behavior is a significant expression of their paradoxical position as citizens who straddle the boundaries of social inclusion and exclusion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Asian American Studies.2bisacsh1 aChang, Gordon H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362548840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625488423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625488/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles